ivardefs.name: code
ivardefs.desc: A computer processable form of the unit in some unit representation system.

ivardefs.name: comparator
ivardefs.desc: How the value should be understood and represented - whether the actual value is greater or less than the stated value due to measurement issues; e.g. if the comparator is "<" , then the real value is < stated value.

ivardefs.name: system
ivardefs.desc: The identification of the system that provides the coded form of the unit.

ivardefs.name: unit
ivardefs.desc: A human-readable form of the unit.

ivardefs.name: value
ivardefs.desc: The value of the measured amount. The value includes an implicit precision in the presentation of the value.

properties.desc: Base StructureDefinition for Quantity Type: A measured amount (or an amount that can potentially be measured). Note that measured amounts include amounts that are not precisely quantified, including amounts involving arbitrary units and floating currencie
